    "user": "Topic: gsqz compression shipping decision\nWrite the explainer with exactly these sections:\n- Overview\n- Shipping thresholds\n\nSource excerpts:\n1. How gsqz decides whether compressed output ships [source: raw/src-c285c500482efa89-private-tmp-wp3-deposit-note-md.md]\n# wp3-deposit-note.md\n---\ntitle: How gsqz decides whether compressed output ships\nsource: agent research via gwiki search + read (wiki parity+ WP3 deposit demo)\n---\n# How gsqz decides whether compressed output ships\nResearched 2026-06-12 by composing `gwiki search` (\"gsqz output compression\nthresholds savings\") and `gwiki read` over the project wiki.\ngsqz wraps a shell command, strips ANSI codes, and matches the command line\nagainst configured pipeline regexes — first match wins; the matched pipeline's\nstep sequence (filter, group, dedup, truncate) is applied to the captured\noutput ([[code/files/crates/gsqz/src/compressor.rs]], provenance\ncrates/gsqz/src/compressor.rs:78-233). The compressor then enforces shipping\nthresholds before the compressed text replaces the original: minimum output\nlength, maximum compressed line count, and a savings ceiling — output that\ncompresses past the 95% savings threshold is treated as suspicious and the\noriginal is kept ([[code/files/crates/gsqz/src/compressor.rs]], provenance\ncrates/gsqz/src/compressor.rs:235-266). `CompressionResult::savings_pct`\nreports the realized savings for daemon metrics\n(crates/gsqz/src/compressor.rs:15-20). The wrapper always exits 0 so the\ncalling LLM reads pass/fail from content, not exit codes\n([[code/modules/crates/gsqz]]).\nCitations:\n- [[code/files/crates/gsqz/src/compressor.rs]] (crates/gsqz/src/compressor.rs)\n- [[code/modules/crates/gsqz]] (crates/gsqz)\n\n"
